      • callbackContextMap

        protected java.util.Map<java.lang.Long,JavetCallbackContext> callbackContextMap
        The Callback context map.

        V8 may not make final callback when V8 context is being recycled. That may result in memory leak. Callback context map is designed for closing that memory leak issue.

        Since:
        0.8.3

      • terminateExecution

        public void terminateExecution()
        Terminate execution.

        Forcefully terminate the current thread of JavaScript execution in the given isolate.

        This method can be used by any thread even if that thread has not acquired the V8 lock with a Locker object.
